sentences: Barbara Ruick (December 23, 1930 – March 3, 1974), also known as Barbara Ruick Williams, was an American actress and singer.
Early years ==
In the 1950s, Ruick starred as Kay in the first LP recording of the songs from George Gershwin and Ira Gershwin's 1926 Broadway musical, Oh, Kay!.

Ruick married actor Robert Horton in Las Vegas, Nevada, on August 22, 1953.
She had co-starred with Horton in the movie Apache War Smoke the previous year.
The couple separated just prior to their second wedding anniversary in 1955 and divorced in 1956, just after he accompanied her to the world premiere of Carousel.
